org.archive.wayback.replay

Class IdentityHttpHeaderProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.archive.wayback.replay.PreservingHttpHeaderProcessor
      • org.archive.wayback.replay.IdentityHttpHeaderProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HttpHeaderProcessor

    public class IdentityHttpHeaderProcessor
extends PreservingHttpHeaderProcessor
    HttpHeaderProcessor which passes through all headers as-is.

    Transfer-Encoding header is an exception. It is always dropped (or preserved by renaming if prefix is non-empty.) This is because Resource classes always produce original content, decoding transfer-encoding.

    TODO: This may not be the best place to drop Transfer-Encoding header. Maybe better done inside Resource classes, who knows it is decoding transfer-encoding.

    Author:
    brad
